[1] Canada (Alberta)
Date: Fri 4 Jul 2014
Source: Metro News [edited]
http://metronews.ca/news/edmonton/1086621/measles-outbreak-over-for-edmonton-zone/


Alberta Health Services has declared the measles outbreak in the Edmonton zone over as of Friday [4 Jul 2014], according to a media release. It was on 29 Apr 2014 that the Alberta Provincial Health Body declared a measles outbreak for the Calgary, Edmonton and central parts of the province. The outbreak has been declared over now in Calgary and central parts of Alberta.

As of Wed 2 Jul 2014, there had been a total of 13 cases of measles in Edmonton, with a total of 31 reported cases across the province.

[Byline: Stephanie Dubois]

