[6] USA (Texas)
Date: Wed 2 Jul 2014
Source: Big Country [abridged, edited]
http://www.bigcountryhomepage.com/story/d/story/2-related-cases-of-the-measles-confirmed-in-tayl/13151/-R5WMTJ5-0SUngZaYhVZjA


The Abilene-Taylor County Public Health Department has confirmed 2 related cases of measles. One case was reported last week, but now health officials are worried for [other] people that may have been exposed to the illness at the Bonzai Japanese Steak House and Sushi Bar in Abilene. The manager at Bonzai spoke to a KTAB Reporter off camera, saying they were notified by the Health Department on Tue 1 Jul 2014 of the possible exposure. The health department says people may have been exposed between 23-28 Jun 2014. The manager also stated that the Health Department contacted all employees, and they have either been vaccinated or show no measles-like symptoms.

