[8] Philippines (Cebu)
Date: Tue 2 Jul 2014
Source: Solar News [edited]
http://www.solarnews.ph/news/regional/2014/07/01/measles-outbreak-declared-in-cebu-prison#.U7Qi3vl_uZY


A measles outbreak was declared in a detention facility in Cebu after dozens of inmates tested positive for the contagious infection. Acting Jail Warden Romeo Manansala of the Cebu Provincial Detention and Rehabilitation Center (CPDRC) said records showed 51 inmates have been infected as of last Wednesday [25 Jun 2014]. Manansala said the 1st suspected cases of measles were identified on 9 Jun 2014. The number increased to more than 20 on 16 Jun 2014.

He added that relatives of inmates are no longer allowed to go beyond the visiting room except for spouses. He also urged the visitors not to bring along children, who are most vulnerable to the measles virus.

