[10] Russia (Tyumen)
Date: Tue 1 Jul 2014
Source: Newsprom.ru [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, abridged, edited]
http://newsprom.ru/news/Obschestvo/199673.html


Another 6 people have become ill with measles in the Tyumen Oblast [Region] during the past week. The total from 8 May to 27 Jun 2014 has reached 38 cases, most of whom had not been vaccinated against the infection. Of these cases, 11 were adults aged from 21 to 49 years; 27 were children, including toddlers up to 12 years of age. The Rospotrebnadzor [Russian consumer rights organisation] for the Tyumen Region reported that only 2 of the 38 cases had been vaccinated, but that was 10 years previously.

As of 27 Jun 2014, 2727 cases of measles had been confirmed by laboratory analysis at the Regional Centre for Surveillance of infectious disease in Novosibirsk; 3 isolates have been sent for genotyping to the National Center for Surveillance of Infectious Disease in Moscow. The results are not yet available.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Previously, in Measles update 23, it was reported that: "Measles 1st appeared in Tyumen 4 years ago. The 1st case in 2014 was detected on 8 May 2014 and by 3 Jun 2014, the total was 26 cases, 8 of whom remain in hospital. Most of the patients were children aged 5 months to 8 years. 24 of the measles cases had not been vaccinated. A total of 1448 contacts, 332 of them children, have been vaccinated. Patients who refused to be hospitalised were observed daily at home by health care workers. Additionally, 62 people received immunoglobulin treatment."

Tyumen is the largest city and the administrative center of Tyumen Oblast (region), Russia. Tyumen was the 1st Russian settlement in Siberia. Founded in 1586 to support Russia's eastward expansion, the city has remained one of the most important industrial and economic centers east of the Ural Mountains. Its location can be found in the maps at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tyumen and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2590806,427. - Mod.CP]

